title: Thirteen dead after bus carrying music group falls into gorge
description: Thirteen people have been killed and 29 others injured after a bus carrying dozens of members of a music troupe fell into a gorge in western India.

title: US ambassador forced to shelter as fighting breaks out in Sudan's capital
description: The US ambassador to Sudan has been forced to take shelter after sustained fighting broke out in the capital Khartoum, as tension between the military and powerful paramilitary forces escalates.

title: 'Concerning' mutations in man's bird flu infection
description: A man in Chile is infected with bird flu that has "concerning" mutations, US health officials have said.

title: US intelligence leaks suspect 'had more online friends than real friends'
description: In his garden there was, what else, but a 'gaming chair'.

title: Japanese PM evacuated after loud explosion heard during outdoor event - reports
description: A loud explosion has been heard at an outdoor event being attended by Japan's prime minister, according to local reports.

title: Three of El Chapo's sons charged over drug trafficking as US tackles overdose crisis
description: Three sons of the notorious drug lord Joaquin "El Chapo" Guzman have been charged over drug trafficking by the US Justice Department.

title: Vladimir Putin closes loophole that allowed Russian men to avoid military service
description: Vladimir Putin has signed a bill allowing authorities to issue electronic mobilisation notices to draftees and reservists.
